        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-10 12:29:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nCurrent implementation of EnvProvider filters empty envs, meaning that if env is defined but has no value it is treated as if it wasn't defined. In case of parameters like request_url empty env is ignored. So in current patchset providing OUTPUT_TYPE as env wouldn't throw exception. I think there are three options to continue:\n1) refactor all such cases to be treated as exceptions\n2) refactor so only output_type case throws exception\n3) accept empty env for default output_type\nWhat do you think Paweł?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
